The paper deals with the problem of attributing cyber-operations, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a formal reasoning system that combines argumentation-based reasoning and probabilistic models, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of logic programming, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper specifically deals with cyber warfare, which suggests the involvement of the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
